reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality for a good price
reviews.reviewText: I used these packing cubes during my recent trip to Mexico. The net part is nice so you can see what’s in the cube. No water resistance though. They helped my clothes stay organized & created a LITTLE bit of room in my backpack. No packing cube is going to make significant space so don’t think they’re a big space saver. They did compress the corners a little bit with minimum bulge to the middle. Zippers didn’t get stuck which is a huge plus. Just make sure you run your finger in front of it when compressing & you’ll have no issues. I took along one medium & two small cubes in a 32L backpack. I could’ve easily fit two more small ones if I didn’t have shoes in my bag. Overall, great quality for the price & perfect for backpackers.
